## "Write Git Commit" Command
When the user says "write git commit", this is a direct command to:
* Review all changes made since the last commit
* Identify the most significant/critical changes
* Create an appropriate commit message following this style guide
* Agents are **NOT** allowed to perform commits unless explicitly told to do so.

## 1. Format
The commit message must follow this exact structure: `type(optional-scope): Summary`

## 2. Type (Mandatory)
The type must be one of the following and must be followed by a colon (`:`):

| Type | Clarification |
| :--- | :--- |
| `feat` | New feature |
| `fix` | Bug fix |
| `refactor` | Internal change |
| `perf` | Performance improvements |
| `build` | Build/export changes |
| `ci` | CI scripts/config changes |
| `chore` | Maintenance tasks |
| `style` | Formatting (white-space, missing semi-colons, etc.) |
| `test` | Unit/play tests |
| `docs` | Documentation |
| `revert` | Undo previous commit |
| `BREAKING` | Major breaking change (use for `feat!` or `fix!`) |
| `art` | 2D/3D assets |
| `anim` | Animations |
| `audio` | Music/SFX/voice |
| `level` | Maps/levels |
| `ui` | Menus/HUD |
| `script` | Dialogue/cutscenes |
| `tool` | Editor/internal tools |
| `design` | Balance/mechanics adjustments |
| `meta` | Project management/process notes |
| `mktg` | Marketing assets |
| `testplay` | Playtest notes/fixes |
| `local` | Localization/translation updates |

## 3. Scope (Optional)
If included, the scope must be enclosed in parentheses `()`. It clarifies the affected part of the project (e.g., `player`, `env`, `audio-system`).

## 4. Summary (Mandatory)
The summary must be **short, imperative sentences** describing the changes made.
* **EX:**
feat(player): Add wall jump ability
- Add wall jump detection
- Add wall jump animation trigger  
- Add wall jump sound effect

## Examples
* `feat(player): Add wall jump ability`
* `art(env): Create desert biome tileset`
* `audio(ui): New SFX for pause menu`
* `fix: Resolve crashing bug in main menu`
* `BREAKING(API): Update game loop to use DeltaTime`
